HYDRO_GEOM_POINTS: Integrated Geographic Objects - Points placed at a specified distance interval along the valley centerline. This distance is a function of the average valley width for a given stream.
HYDRO_POINTS: IGOs attributed with values for hydrology calculated within a single DGO or an aggregation of DGOs.
HYDRO_GEOM_LINES: NHD Flowlines that have been intersected with land ownership, road and rail.
HYDRO_LINES: NHD Flowlines attributed with values for physical characteristics and hydrology
HYDRO_GEOM_DGOS: Discrete Geographic Objects - The valley bottom split into a sampling frame of polygons where the IGO points are at the center of each polygon.
HYDRO_DGOS: DGOs attributed with values for physical stream characteristics and hydrology within the DGO extent.
